radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung bases are clear with no focal consolidation or pleural effusion. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, bilateral adrenal glands appear unremarkable. Both kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically without evidence of hydronephrosis or renal calculi. The intra-abdominal vasculature is unremarkable. There is no free air or free fluid within the abdomen. The appendix appears fluid-filled, measuring up to 10 mm with minimal mucosal hyperemia and mild periappendiceal fat stranding consistent with appendicitis. The bladder appears unremarkable. The endometrial cavity of the uterus shows minimal fluid. A left adnexal cyst is identified. Visualized osseous structures show no focal lytic or sclerotic lesions suspicious for malignancy.
